reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Fit exactly as the OEM parts did. Felt durable when I installed them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This is a part which I believe breaks easily. This replaced the Oem one exactly and was easy to install. The only hard part was figuring where the little retainer clip went exactly

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It appears to work -- does what it says it does
reviews.reviewText: Installed a pair yesterday after reviewing several YouTube videos to supplement sellers video.Removing and replacing two, took 30 minutes and required only a screwdriver and some pliers.The parts seem to be sturdy and fit into the Kitchenaid without any modification.A minor complaint: The kit does not include the adjuster protective housing which is made from the same aging plastic as the adjuster's themselves. So this leaves a weak point in the repair. The seller video doesn't cover this detail, and at first I thought they had left out some parts.PROS: Installation was pretty easy and nothing required modification. The parts fit nicely and did not interfere with the drawer mechanism as some review suggests they may.CONS: No instructions on how to adjust or level the completed repair. No replacement 'adjuster housing' is provided, so if that part is also defective, your repair will be in vain.We'll see how this holds up. The OEM parts began to fail after about 5 years as I recall.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Need instructions to install.
reviews.reviewText: Very good quality product and economical. Received in two days. Only problem is there really needs to be instructions on removing the broken part from the dishwasher and installing the new part. I had to go to YouTube for instructions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The fit was good for my KitchenAid KDPE334GPS0 dishwasher. Install was 15 min and fairly straightforward. Time will tell on the quality but OEM part didnt last and I expect this will last at least as long or better. I typically buy OEM parts but honestly if the originals don't last long and replacement is 6-7 times the cost of a 3rd party replacement then why waste the money. I recommend this kit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My Kitchen Aid dishwasher was simply falling apart inside. That's a shame since it's not that old. I got this kit to rebuild the top rack and it works just fine. The fit is almost as good as the oem parts and much cheaper. I hope it lasts!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Part for Kitchenaid Diswasher
reviews.reviewText: The part is exactly the same as our Kitchenaid dishwasher part at a fraction of the cost. This rack adjuster arm breaks often unfortunately. Got tired of paying service calls to repairman exceeding $200 with the part after waiting a week. It was a breeze to order this on Amazon and it arrived the next day. We followed instructions from YouTube and replaced the part not saying it’s fun but if you want a working dishwasher you can’t beat this deal.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Needs a little work
reviews.reviewText: The negative reviewers were correct, these are well made parts except the tabs that hold the rack to the slides are too thick. These tabs did not work on my dishwasher because they're too thick to fit into the slides. I had to take a dremel tool with a sanding drum and make them skinnier. Fortunately, it didn't take long and afterwards they fit perfectly. I bought them knowing this was possible problem because the parts get good reviews otherwise. Amazon also was the only seller who could have them at my door in two days. All in all, except for the one thing, these are a good value. Half the price of OEM.

If you were like me:1) frustrated when your rack snapped on your high end dishwasher2) considering “just hire a guy” to fix it3) not a handy personWell… I ordered this product and youtubed the installation. Super easyWorks great. Buy with confidence

This part on my KitchenAid dishwasher is poorly designed and the OEM and replacement parts are not satisfactory. The OEM rack adjusters lasted about two years before both sides broke at the locating tabs and push button locks. I ordered two different replacements which only lasted about a month each. This product claims to be "improved", so lets hope that is correct. It has a long warranty, so I hope I don't need to use it. The parts were harder to install than the other replacements, so I am hoping that means better durability. The install is very difficult and not intuitive. Thanks for the posting of a "how to" video, which I would not have managed without. I will update if any changes to my review.
Easy installation. Will see if they last long then the factory ones
Exactly like the original. You won’t be able to tell the difference. Seems to be more durable than the original OEM.
